## Security Policy for Pyvtron Shaders

Thank you for your interest in the security of Pyvtron Shaders.  
If you discover a security vulnerability or issue, please report it responsibly so we can address it promptly.

## How to report a security issue

you can contact us through our [issue tracker](https://github.com/pyvtron/pyvtron-shaders/issues) if you prefer not to report a confidential issue. Please label the issue as "Security" or "Security Issue".

## What we need from your report

To help us investigate and fix the issue quickly, please include:

- Description of the problem / vulnerability  
- Steps to reproduce the issue  
- Affected version(s) of Pyvtron Shaders  
- Possible impact and risks  
- Sample code or logs, if available

## Our process

- We acknowledge receipt of your report within 48 hours.  
- We work on resolving the issue as soon as possible.  
- Security fixes are published and documented in a timely manner.  
- You may be credited as the discoverer of the vulnerability, either anonymously or by name.

## Code of conduct

We kindly ask all security researchers to act responsibly and avoid disclosing vulnerabilities publicly before we have had a chance to fix them.

Thank you for helping us make Pyvtron Shaders more secure!

